create ec2 server in instance type of t3.medium – create key pair – create 
Go to created ec2  >> security >> sg id >>  inbound rule >> ssh in default >> add rule custom tcp or all tcp – port range: 8080 – source : anywhere ipv4 

### Adds the official Jenkins stable repository to your system so yum/dnf can find the Jenkins package
sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
### Imports the GPG signing key for the Jenkins repo
sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
sudo yum upgrade
###JAVA INSTALLATION
sudo yum install -y java-17-amazon-corretto
Java --version
sudo yum install -y Jenkins
sudo systemctl enable jenkins
systemctl enable jenkins
### Jenkins will begin listening on port 8080 by default and generate an initial admin password
sudo systemctl start jenkins
sudo systemctl status jenkins

